This paper discusses the security and usability of a fallback authentication method, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves a user study to evaluate the usability of the proposed method, which relates to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of autobiographical location data for authentication may also fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI) or cyber-physical systems (cs.CY). Finally, the use of an Android application for the proposed method may also relate to multimedia (cs.MM).
